==Issues with Faircoin Value System and Governance==

We are summarizing an anonymous evaluation about the internal problems with the project:

"* Faircoin is just a fork of bitcoin, replacing ProofOfWork by ProofOfAuthority, where the authority is the 'assembly' that basically is Enric and some friends

* Lot of people have lost lot of money, and currently they have a debt with lot of commerces that accepted faircoin during months, basing that acceptance in the promise from Faircoop to exchange the received faircoins to € (based in Faircoop liquidity box), but that box was empty.. so nobody from the producers and commerces can get the € ; one of the biggest problems was that there was the market price, and an assembly price. The current market price is arround 0.01€, while the assembly price is 1.20€ (and nobody accepts that price)

* decisions are made through infinite telegram group meetings, where participation for everybody was difficult, and at the end lot of the decisions were taken by last people standing (because the rest were tired and disconnected) ; the governance system in Faircoop is fatigue consensus ("consenso por cansancio") which refears to that the decision are taken in infinite meetings in telegram groups, where after 4 hours of meeting more than 70% of the people has disconnected

(email, December 2019)

